sentences: Priscilla Betti (real name: Préscillia Betti; born August 2, 1989 in Nice), formerly known as simply Priscilla, is a French singer, dancer and actress.
In 2008–2011 she played the main part in the French musical TV series Chante!.
Priscilla Betti was born on August 2, 1989 into a family living in Nice (Alpes-Maritimes).

When Priscilla was eleven years old, she visited the show Drôles de petits champions, February 23, 2001, on TF1, and was noticed by a producer from the American company Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer, Patrick Debort.
Betti's first album, Cette Vie nouvelle, was released in June 2002.
Her second album, Priscilla was released only six months after the first one, in December 2002.
Betti's third album, Une Fille comme moi, was released in early 2004.
Betti's fourth album, Bric à brac, was released in the summer of 2005.
Starting from February 2008 Betti played the main part in the musical TV series Chante!
on France 2 in the block programming KD2A. The fourth and last season aired in 2011.
Songs from the first season were released as Betti's fifth album, Casse comme du verre, in December 2007.
In the fall of 2014 Betti made her stage debut as the lead in a stage adaptation of the musical Flashdance which was shown in Théâtre du Gymnase in Paris until March 2015.
